{"build_type":"library","description":"The single append-only writer of the kernel error ring (DESIGN: error-ring-journal). Pure CPU: atomic-fetch-add the monotonic cursor, wrap by mask, write the 64-byte record {seq,code,task_id,rip,name[32]}. The faulting binary name is COPIED INLINE (32 bytes from name_ptr into rec+32, truncated + NUL-terminated at offset 63) so the record is self-contained for audit; name_ptr==0 leaves an empty inline name. Lock-free; concurrent tasks get distinct slots. No Linux. Edit this package to change the record/journal everywhere. [PATCH: error-ring uses broadcast doorbell (wake all readers), not counting semaphore.]","module_name":"append-error-record-into-ring-buffer","package_name":"append-error-record-into-ring-buffer","function_definitions":{"append-error-record-into-ring-buffer":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"code","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"task_id","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"rip","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"name_ptr","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"base","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":105553116266496},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"mask","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1023},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"hdr","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":64},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"recsz","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":256},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zeroidx","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declarat